<subSubSection id="6FAC69891B554E5BFF59E9F2A8C5FCD6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="27093A021B554E5BFF59E9F2AE49FCBE" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,858]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="15C2E6101B554E5BFF59E9F2AD55FC85" bold="true" box="[198,339,751,777]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
Aspro­ = Gk. white + ­ spilos = Gk. spot. The species is named for the white pollinose spots on the lateral surfaces of tergites 
<number id="917E28251B554E5BFD84E805AE4DFCBE" box="[539,587,792,818]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
